main event: Numerous fishing vessels off the West Coast of Florida observed a brilliant flare moving in a southeast direction for 30 to 40 minutes, which was believed to be a rocket from Cape Canaveral. The sighting was also confirmed by the Miami Coast Guard and supported by transmissions overheard on 2182 KCS.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for a significant duration of 30 to 40 minutes, allowing for ample observation time.
The flare was observed by numerous fishing vessels, indicating multiple credible witnesses.
Supporting transmissions overheard on 2182 KCS confirmed the sighting and its association with a rocket from Cape Canaveral.
The location of the sighting was off the West Coast of Florida, a region known for high rocket and missile testing activity at Cape Canaveral.
The official report seems to categorize the sighting as a 'Brilliant flare' and suggests it was likely a rocket from Cape Canaveral.
sighted object: brilliant flare moving in a southeast direction
